sentence: The First Trust Consumer Staples AlphaDEX Fund ETF is seeing unusually high volume in afternoon trading Tuesday, with over 226,000 shares traded versus three month average volume of about 55,000.
Shares of FXG were up about 0.5% on the day.

Components of that ETF with the highest volume on Tuesday were Rite Aid, trading down about 1.5% with over 4.9 million shares changing hands so far this session, and Procter & Gamble, up about 0.7% on volume of over 4.1 million shares.
US Foods Holding is the component faring the best Tuesday, higher by about 2.7% on the day.
